com.github.robtimus.io.stream

Class LimitOutputStream

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.OutputStream
      • com.github.robtimus.io.stream.LimitOutputStream
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, Flushable, AutoCloseable

    public final class LimitOutputStream
extends OutputStream
    An output stream that limits the number of bytes that can be written to another output stream.

    If a write call causes the limit to be exceeded and the limit output stream is configured to throw an exception, the call will lead to a LimitExceededException to be thrown.

    Author:
    Rob Spoor

      • LimitOutputStream

        public LimitOutputStream(OutputStream output,
                         long limit)
        Creates a new limit output stream. This output stream will discard any excess bytes.
        Parameters:
        output - The output stream for which to limit the number of bytes that can be written.
        limit - The maximum number of bytes that can be written.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - If the given output stream is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - If the given limit is negative.

      • LimitOutputStream

        public LimitOutputStream(OutputStream output,
                         long limit,
                         LimitExceededStrategy strategy)
        Creates a new limit output stream.
        Parameters:
        output - The output stream for which to limit the number of bytes that can be written.
        limit - The maximum number of bytes that can be written.
        strategy - The strategy to follow when the maximum number of bytes has exceeded.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - If the given output stream or strategy is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - If the given limit is negative.
